    "message_2": "To solve the given initial value problem using the fourth-order Runge-Kutta method with h=0.1, we will follow these steps:\n\n1. Define the function for the differential equation: f(t, y) = -2y + 1\n2. Initialize the variables: t0 = 0, y0 = 0, h = 0.1\n3. Iterate through the interval using the Runge-Kutta method.\n\nThe fourth-order Runge-Kutta method involves the following calculations for each iteration:\n\nk1 = h * f(t, y)\nk2 = h * f(t + h/2, y + k1/2)\nk3 = h * f(t + h/2, y + k2/2)\nk4 = h * f(t + h, y + k3)\ny_new = y + (k1 + 2*k2 + 2*k3 + k4) / 6\nt_new = t + h\n\nNow, let's perform the calculations for the given problem:\n\nIteration 1:\nt0 = 0, y0 = 0\nk1 = 0.1 * (-2*0 + 1) = 0.1\nk2 = 0.1 * (-2*(0 + 0.1/2) + 1) = 0.09\nk3 = 0.1 * (-2*(0 + 0.09/2) + 1) = 0.091\nk4 = 0.1 * (-2*(0 + 0.091) + 1) = 0.0818\ny1 = 0 + (0.1 + 2*0.09 + 2*0.091 + 0.0818) / 6 = 0.0903\nt1 = 0 + 0.1 = 0.1\n\nIteration 2:\nt1 = 0.1, y1 = 0.0903\nk1 = 0.1 * (-2*0.0903 + 1) = 0.08186\nk2 = 0.1 * (-2*(0.0903 + 0.08186/2) + 1) = 0.074878\nk3 = 0.1 * (-2*(0.0903 + 0.074878/2) + 1) = 0.075796\nk4 = 0.1 * (-2*(0.0903 + 0.075796) + 1) = 0.0693188\ny2 = 0.0903 + (0.08186 + 2*0.074878 + 2*0.075796 + 0.0693188) / 6 = 0.164878\nt2 = 0.1 + 0.1 = 0.2\n\nIteration 3:\nt2 = 0.2, y2 = 0.164878\nk1 = 0.1 * (-2*0.164878 + 1) = 0.067044\nk2 = 0.1 * (-2*(0.164878 + 0.067044/2) + 1) = 0.0617598\nk3 = 0.1 * (-2*(0.164878 + 0.0617598/2) + 1) = 0.0623738\nk4 = 0.1 * (-2*(0.164878 + 0.0623738) + 1) = 0.05753356\ny3 = 0.164878 + (0.067044 + 2*0.0617598 + 2*0.0623738 + 0.05753356) / 6 = 0.225758\nt3 = 0.2 + 0.1 = 0.3\n\nIteration 4:\nt3 = 0.3, y3 = 0.225758\nk1 = 0.1 * (-2*0.225758 + 1) = 0.054484\nk2 = 0.1 * (-2*(0.225758 + 0.054484/2) + 1) = 0.0505178\nk3 = 0.1 * (-2*(0.225758 + 0.0505178/2) + 1) = 0.0508762\nk4 = 0.1 * (-2*(0.225758 + 0.0508762) + 1) = 0.04698944\ny4 = 0.225758 + (0.054484 + 2*0.0505178 + 2*0.0508762 + 0.04698944) / 6 = 0.275758\nt4 = 0.3 + 0.1 = 0.4\n\nIteration 5:\nt4 = 0.4, y4 = 0.275758\nk1 = 0.1 * (-2*0.275758 + 1) = 0.044484\nk2 = 0.1 * (-2*(0.275758 + 0.044484/2) + 1) = 0.0415178\nk3 = 0.1 * (-2*(0.275758 + 0.0415178/2) + 1) = 0.0418762\nk4 = 0.1 * (-2*(0.275758 + 0.0418762) + 1) = 0.03898944\ny5 = 0.275758 + (0.044484 + 2*0.0415178 + 2*0.0418762 + 0.03898944) / 6 = 0.316758\nt5 = 0.4 + 0.1 = 0.5\n\nSo, the solution of the differential equation y'=-2y+1 over the interval 0≤t≤0.5 using the fourth-order Runge-Kutta method with h=0.1 is:\n\ny(0.1) = 0.0903\ny(0.2) = 0.164878\ny(0.3) = 0.225758\ny(0.4) = 0.275758\ny(0.5) = 0.316758"
